 {"id":"remote_compilation_helper-7ds","title":"Epic: Rich rch status Command for Operational Visibility","description":"## Overview

Implement a comprehensive `rch status` command that shows the complete state of the RCH system at a glance: daemon health, worker status, slot availability, recent build history, and any issues requiring attention.

## Problem Statement

Users currently have limited visibility into RCH's operational state:
- Is the daemon running?
- Which workers are healthy vs degraded?
- Why did my build fail or run slowly?
- Is RCH actually being used for my builds?

Without observability, users can't diagnose issues or build confidence in the system.

## Goals

1. Show daemon status (running, pid, uptime)
2. Show all workers with health, slots, speed scores
3. Show recent build history (last N builds with outcomes)
4. Highlight any issues requiring attention
5. Support both human-readable and JSON output formats

## Design

