-{"id":"remote_compilation_helper-9pw","title":"Epic: Circuit Breaker Pattern with Auto-Recovery","description":"## Overview

Implement the circuit breaker pattern for worker health management. After N consecutive failures, "trip" the circuit and stop sending requests to that worker. After a cool-down period, enter "half-open" state and probe the worker. If probe succeeds, reset to healthy; if probe fails, re-trip the circuit.

## Problem Statement

Current health check behavior:
- Workers marked `Unreachable` after 3 consecutive failures
- Health checks continue running for all workers
- No backoff between checks for failing workers
- Recovery may not be smooth - worker could flap between states

Problems with current approach:
- Failing workers continue receiving health checks at same rate (wastes resources)
- No "soft" recovery testing before returning worker to full rotation
- Status can flap rapidly if worker is intermittently available
- No exponential backoff means sustained load on failing infrastructure

## Goals

1. Implement circuit breaker state machine (Closed → Open → Half-Open)
2. Add exponential backoff for health checks on open circuits
3. Probe workers in half-open state before full recovery
4. Integrate circuit state with worker selection (skip open circuits)
5. Expose circuit state in status API

## Design

### State Machine
```
                    success
                ┌───────────────────────────────────────┐
                │                                       │
                ▼                                       │
┌────────────────────┐  N failures  ┌──────────────┐  cooldown   ┌─────────────┐
│ CLOSED (Healthy)   ├─────────────►│ OPEN         ├────────────►│ HALF_OPEN   │
│ Normal operation   │              │ Skip worker  │             │ Probe only  │
└────────────────────┘              └──────────────┘             └──────┬──────┘
